[
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "p"
      },
      {
        "text": "Yahweh’s",
        "foot": {
          "type": "stu",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "“Yahweh” is God’s proper Name, sometimes rendered “LORD” (all caps) in other translations."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "text": "word that came to Joel, the son of Pethuel."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Hear this, you elders,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and listen, all you inhabitants of the land!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Has this ever happened in your days,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "or in the days of your fathers?"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Tell your children about it,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and have your children tell their children,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and their children, another generation."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "What the swarming locust has left, the great locust has eaten."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "What the great locust has left, the grasshopper has eaten."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "What the grasshopper has left, the caterpillar has eaten."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Wake up, you drunkards, and weep!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Wail, all you drinkers of wine, because of the sweet wine,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for it is cut off from your mouth."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "For a nation has come up on my land, strong, and without number."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "His teeth are the teeth of a lion,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and he has the fangs of a lioness."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "He has laid my vine waste,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and stripped my fig tree."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "He has stripped its bark, and thrown it away."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Its branches are made white."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Mourn like a virgin dressed in sackcloth"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the husband of her youth!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "The meal offering and the drink offering are cut off from Yahweh’s house."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The priests, Yahweh’s ministers, mourn."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "The field is laid waste."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The land mourns, for the grain is destroyed,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The new wine has dried up,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the oil languishes."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Be confounded, you farmers!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Wail, you vineyard keepers,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the wheat and for the barley;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the harvest of the field has perished."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "The vine has dried up, and the fig tree withered—"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "the pomegranate tree, the palm tree also, and the apple tree,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "even all of the trees of the field are withered;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for joy has withered away from the sons of men."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Put on sackcloth and mourn, you priests!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Wail, you ministers of the altar."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Come, lie all night in sackcloth, you ministers of my God,",
        "foot": {
          "type": "trn",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The Hebrew word rendered “God” is “[hebrew]אֱלֹהִ֑ים[/hebrew]” (Elohim)."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the meal offering and the drink offering are withheld from your God’s house."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Sanctify a fast."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Call a solemn assembly."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Gather the elders and all the inhabitants of the land to the house of Yahweh, your God,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and cry to Yahweh."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Alas for the day!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "For the day of Yahweh is at hand,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and it will come as destruction from the Almighty."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Isn’t the food cut off before our eyes,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "joy and gladness from the house of our God?"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "The seeds rot under their clods."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The granaries are laid desolate."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The barns are broken down, for the grain has withered."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "How the animals groan!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The herds of livestock are perplexed, because they have no pasture."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Yes, the flocks of sheep are made desolate."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Yahweh, I cry to you,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the fire has devoured the pastures of the wilderness,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the flame has burned all the trees of the field."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Yes, the animals of the field pant to you,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the water brooks have dried up,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the fire has devoured the pastures of the wilderness."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "p"
      },
      {
        "text": "Blow the trumpet in Zion,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and sound an alarm in my holy mountain!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Let all the inhabitants of the land tremble,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the day of Yahweh comes,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for it is close at hand:"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "A day of darkness and gloominess,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "a day of clouds and thick darkness."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "As the dawn spreading on the mountains,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "a great and strong people;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "there has never been the like,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "neither will there be any more after them,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "even to the years of many generations."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "A fire devours before them,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and behind them, a flame burns."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The land is as the garden of Eden before them,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and behind them, a desolate wilderness."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Yes, and no one has escaped them."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Their appearance is as the appearance of horses,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and they run as horsemen."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 5,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Like the noise of chariots on the tops of the mountains, they leap,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "like the noise of a flame of fire that devours the stubble,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "like a strong people set in battle array."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 6,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "At their presence the peoples are in anguish."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "All faces have grown pale."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 7,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "They run like mighty men."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "They climb the wall like warriors."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "They each march in his line, and they don’t swerve off course."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 8,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "One doesn’t jostle another."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "They each march in their own path."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "They burst through the defenses"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and don’t break ranks."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 9,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "They rush on the city."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "They run on the wall."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "They climb up into the houses."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "They enter in at the windows like thieves."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 10,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "The earth quakes before them."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The heavens tremble."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The sun and the moon are darkened,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the stars withdraw their shining."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 11,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Yahweh thunders his voice before his army,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for his forces are very great;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for he is strong who obeys his command;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the day of Yahweh is great and very awesome,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and who can endure it?"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 12,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "“Yet even now,” says Yahweh, “turn to me with all your heart,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and with fasting, and with weeping, and with mourning.”"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 13,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Tear your heart and not your garments,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and turn to Yahweh, your God;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for he is gracious and merciful,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "slow to anger, and abundant in loving kindness,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and relents from sending calamity."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 14,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Who knows? He may turn and relent,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and leave a blessing behind him,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "even a meal offering and a drink offering to Yahweh, your God."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 15,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Blow the trumpet in Zion!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Sanctify a fast."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Call a solemn assembly."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 16,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Gather the people."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Sanctify the assembly."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Assemble the elders."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Gather the children, and those who nurse from breasts."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Let the bridegroom go out of his room,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the bride out of her chamber."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 17,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Let the priests, the ministers of Yahweh, weep between the porch and the altar,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and let them say, “Spare your people, Yahweh,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and don’t give your heritage to reproach,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "that the nations should rule over them."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Why should they say among the peoples,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "‘Where is their God?’ ”"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 18,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Then Yahweh was jealous for his land,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and had pity on his people."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 19,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Yahweh answered his people,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "“Behold,",
        "foot": {
          "type": "trn",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "“Behold”, from “[hebrew]הִנֵּה[/hebrew]”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an interjection."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "text": "I will send you grain, new wine, and oil,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and you will be satisfied with them;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and I will no more make you a reproach among the nations."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 20,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "But I will remove the northern army far away from you,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and will drive it into a barren and desolate land,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "its front into the eastern sea,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and its back into the western sea;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and its stench will come up,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and its bad smell will rise.”"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Surely he has done great things."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 21,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Land, don’t be afraid."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Be glad and rejoice, for Yahweh has done great things."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 22,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Don’t be afraid, you animals of the field;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the pastures of the wilderness spring up,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the tree bears its fruit."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "The fig tree and the vine yield their strength."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 23,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "p"
      },
      {
        "text": "“Be glad then, you children of Zion,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and rejoice in Yahweh, your God;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for he gives you the early rain in just measure,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and he causes the rain to come down for you,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "the early rain and the latter rain, as before."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 24,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "The threshing floors will be full of wheat,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the vats will overflow with new wine and oil."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 25,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "I will restore to you the years that the swarming locust has eaten,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "the great locust, the grasshopper, and the caterpillar,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "my great army, which I sent among you."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 26,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "You will have plenty to eat and be satisfied,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and will praise the name of Yahweh, your God,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "who has dealt wondrously with you;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and my people will never again be disappointed."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 27,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "You will know that I am among Israel,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and that I am Yahweh, your God, and there is no one else;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and my people will never again be disappointed."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 28,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "p"
      },
      {
        "text": "“It will happen afterward, that I will pour out my Spirit on all flesh;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and your sons and your daughters will prophesy."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Your old men will dream dreams."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Your young men will see visions."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 29,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "And also on the servants and on the handmaids in those days,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "I will pour out my Spirit."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 30,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "I will show wonders in the heavens and in the earth:"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "blood, fire, and pillars of smoke."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 31,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "The sun will be turned into darkness,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the moon into blood,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "before the great and terrible day of Yahweh comes."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 32,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "It will happen that whoever will call on Yahweh’s name shall be saved;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for in Mount Zion and in Jerusalem there will be those who escape,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "as Yahweh has said,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and among the remnant, those whom Yahweh calls."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "p"
      },
      {
        "text": "“For, behold, in those days,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and in that time,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "when I restore the fortunes of Judah and Jerusalem,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "I will gather all nations,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and will bring them down into the valley of Jehoshaphat;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and I will execute judgment on them there for my people,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and for my heritage, Israel, whom they have scattered among the nations."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "They have divided my land,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "and have cast lots for my people,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and have given a boy for a prostitute,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and sold a girl for wine, that they may drink."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "p"
      },
      {
        "text": "“Yes, and what are you to me, Tyre and Sidon,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and all the regions of Philistia?"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Will you repay me?"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "And if you repay me,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "I will swiftly and speedily return your repayment on your own head."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 5,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Because you have taken my silver and my gold,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and have carried my finest treasures into your temples,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 6,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "and have sold the children of Judah and the children of Jerusalem to the sons of the Greeks,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "that you may remove them far from their border."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 7,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Behold, I will stir them up out of the place where you have sold them,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and will return your repayment on your own head;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 8,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "and I will sell your sons and your daughters into the hands of the children of Judah,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and they will sell them to the men of Sheba,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "to a faraway nation,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for Yahweh has spoken it.”"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 9,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "p"
      },
      {
        "text": "Proclaim this among the nations:"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "“Prepare for war!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Stir up the mighty men."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Let all the warriors draw near."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Let them come up."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 10,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Beat your plowshares into swords,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and your pruning hooks into spears."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Let the weak say, ‘I am strong.’"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 11,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Hurry and come, all you surrounding nations,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and gather yourselves together.”"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Cause your mighty ones to come down there, Yahweh."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 12,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "“Let the nations arouse themselves,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and come up to the valley of Jehoshaphat;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for there I will sit to judge all the surrounding nations."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 13,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Put in the sickle;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the harvest is ripe."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Come, tread, for the wine press is full,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "the vats overflow, for their wickedness is great.”"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 14,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Multitudes, multitudes in the valley of decision!"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "For the day of Yahweh is near in the valley of decision."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 15,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "The sun and the moon are darkened,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the stars withdraw their shining."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 16,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Yahweh will roar from Zion,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and thunder from Jerusalem;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the heavens and the earth will shake;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "but Yahweh will be a refuge to his people,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and a stronghold to the children of Israel."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 17,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "“So you will know that I am Yahweh, your God,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "dwelling in Zion, my holy mountain."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "Then Jerusalem will be holy,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and no strangers will pass through her any more."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 18,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "It will happen in that day,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "that the mountains will drop down sweet wine,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "the hills will flow with milk,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "all the brooks of Judah will flow with waters;"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and a fountain will flow out from Yahweh’s house,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and will water the valley of Shittim."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 19,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Egypt will be a desolation"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and Edom will be a desolate wilderness,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the violence done to the children of Judah,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "because they have shed innocent blood in their land."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 20,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "But Judah will be inhabited forever,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "and Jerusalem from generation to generation."
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "book": "Joel",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 21,
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "I will cleanse their blood"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "that I have not cleansed,"
      },
      {
        "type": "n"
      },
      {
        "text": "for Yahweh dwells in Zion.”"
      }
    ]
  }
]